   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>IN THE SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Our organic union with the Lord is also in the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Christ and the Spirit are not two separate persons.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>They are one person.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>This is a divine mystery that is beyond human understanding.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Christ is the Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b; 2 Cor 3:17 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The One who died on the cross, resurrected from the dead, and ascended to the heavens is Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>But this Christ enters into us as the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>When we call O Lord Jesus, the Spirit gets into us.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>When we call the name of a person, we get the person of that name.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>If I call a brother s name, that brother will respond to me.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The name and the person are one.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>When we call on the name of Jesus, we get His person the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>When we believed into the Lord Jesus, we did not call on the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>We called on the Lord Jesus and we received Him as the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>First Corinthians 15:45b says, The last Adam became a life-giving Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The name of the last Adam is Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>We called on the objective name of Jesus, and the subjective Spirit came into us.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>This is because the last Adam in His resurrection was transfigured into the Spirit, that is, He became the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Spirit and Jesus Christ are one.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>THE ONE SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>BEING THE REALITY OF THE ONE BODY</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Ephesians 4:4 says that there is one Body and one Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The Body is the organism, and the Spirit is the reality of the organism.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>There is one organism and one reality.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>If we do not have the Spirit, we do not have the organism.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>As long as the Spirit is with us, we have the organism.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The Very Essence of the Triune God</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The Spirit, who is the reality of the organism of the Triune God, is the very essence of the Triune God.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>John 4:24 says that God is Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>We may say that the essence of a certain table is wood.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The Triune God also has His essence.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>A certain table is wood, and the Triune God is Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The Spirit is His essence.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The Very Reality of God</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>The Spirit is also the very reality of God 1 John 5:6b; John 16:13 .</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>If we do not have the Spirit, we do not have God in reality.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>We may have God only in terminology and not as reality.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>The reality of God is the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>When we called on the name of Jesus, God Himself came into us as the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Now God is in us.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>God dwells in us, and we dwell in Him because we have the Spirit who is the reality of God.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>The Reaching of the Triune God to Man</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>The Spirit is the reaching of the Triune God to man Eph 2:18 .</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Seemingly, God is far away from us in the third heavens.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>How could He reach us?</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>He reaches us not as the Father or as the Son, but as the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>Every Christian has experienced God reaching him as the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>The Spirit is the realization of the Son, and the Son is the embodiment of the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>In other words, the Father is embodied in the Son, and the Son is realized as the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>If we have the Spirit, we have the Son and the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>When we called on the name of the Lord Jesus, the Spirit entered into us.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>The Spirit within us is the Triune God because the Spirit is the realization of the Son, who is the embodiment of the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>The Processed and Compound Spirit</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>The Spirit is also the processed and compound Spirit Phil 1:19 .</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Because the Spirit has been processed, He is a compound Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>The Spirit has passed through the process of God s incarnation.</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>When God became a man, He picked up humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='59' RSNT='1' SNO='59'>In eternity past He was only God without humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='60' RSNT='1' SNO='60'>But in His incarnation, humanity was added to divinity.</S>
   <S PAR='61' RSNT='1' SNO='61'>Incarnation was a process for God to add humanity to Himself.</S>
   <S PAR='62' RSNT='1' SNO='62'>Then God with humanity went to the cross and died.</S>
   <S PAR='63' RSNT='1' SNO='63'>His all-inclusive death was also a wonderful process.</S>
   <S PAR='64' RSNT='1' SNO='64'>God passed through death in humanity, in the flesh, in man.</S>
   <S PAR='65' RSNT='1' SNO='65'>In the shell of a human body, He went through His all-inclusive death, and He was raised up in resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='66' RSNT='1' SNO='66'>He went into death, walked through death, and came out of death.</S>
   <S PAR='67' RSNT='1' SNO='67'>Death could not hold Him because He is the resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='68' RSNT='1' SNO='68'>He raised Himself up from among the dead and entered into resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='69' RSNT='1' SNO='69'>He is now a God of divinity, of humanity, of incarnation, of an all-inclusive death, and of a wonderful, excellent, transcendent resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='70' RSNT='1' SNO='70'>The name of our God is Jesus Christ, and when we called upon Him, the Spirit as the processed God came into us.</S>
   <S PAR='71' RSNT='1' SNO='71'>The Spirit is the processed God and the compound Spirit that has been compounded with divinity, humanity, incarnation, death, and resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='72' RSNT='1' SNO='72'>When someone cooks a feast, the food of the feast passes through many processes.</S>
   <S PAR='73' RSNT='1' SNO='73'>The food may be salted, other spices may be added to it, and then it is cooked.</S>
   <S PAR='74' RSNT='1' SNO='74'>There is a great difference between a cooked fish and a raw fish.</S>
   <S PAR='75' RSNT='1' SNO='75'>A cooked fish is a processed fish that is good for eating.</S>
   <S PAR='76' RSNT='1' SNO='76'>The very Spirit whom we have received is the processed Spirit, not the raw Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='77' RSNT='1' SNO='77'>He is the cooked Spirit, the cooked God.</S>
   <S PAR='78' RSNT='1' SNO='78'>Because the Spirit has been cooked, processed, He is edible, refreshing, and nourishing.</S>
   <S PAR='79' RSNT='1' SNO='79'>The processed Spirit of God has come into us as a rich feast for our enjoyment.</S>
   </TEXT>
